Overview: 

Hong Kong super cop Jackie Chan is back on the beat, but this time he's not alone. Partnered with kung fu fighting Mainland Chinese lady cop Michelle Yeoh, Jackie risks life and limb to inflitrate an international arms smuggling racket. The film travels all over Southeast Asia, and features some incredible stunts including a motorcycle jump onto a moving train. The beautiful Maggie Cheung plays Chan's girlfriend and adds an interesting element to the plot when she appears at the most inopportune moments. The ingenuity of the stunts alone makes this film worth watching. Unlike some Chan movies, this one actually has a plot.
